---
alwaysApply: true
---

- use mixins for reusable styles
- use variables for reusable values
- use functions for reusable calculations
- use @use 'sass:map' to access map values
- use @use 'sass:math' to access math functions
- use @use 'sass:string' to access string functions
- use @use 'sass:list' to access list functions
- use @use 'sass:color' to access color functions
- never use @import use @use
- never use hardcoded hex colors or css variables, use the file variables.scss to access the colors
- never hardcode font sizes or text colors, the typography.scss files handles this
- avoid duplication of code the globals.scss or mixins.scss is for that